  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\n\r\nSince v1.14.3, Nethermind will attempt to push metrics when metrics are enabled. This generates frequent errors in a pull-based setup.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n\r\nA flag that disables metrics push, independent of enabling metrics pull.\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\n\r\nCurrently working around this by setting the interval to \"999999\" seconds\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n\r\nAs per Prometheus docs:\r\n\r\n\"\r\nFirst of all, the Pushgateway is not capable of turning Prometheus into a push-based monitoring system. For a general description of use cases for the Pushgateway, please read [When To Use The Pushgateway](https://prometheus.io/docs/practices/pushing/).\r\n\"\r\n\r\nAnd:\r\n\r\n\"\r\nUsually, the only valid use case for the Pushgateway is for capturing the outcome of a service-level batch job. A \"service-level\" batch job is one which is not semantically related to a specific machine or job instance (for example, a batch job that deletes a number of users for an entire service).\r\n\"\r\n",
